This paper deals with the problem of probabilistic inference in databases, which is a core topic in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge compilation, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for efficient reasoning. The paper introduces a new technique for constructing lineage representations, which involves decomposable circuits, a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and the use of negation, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC), respectively.
